article.headline: James Madison 62, San Diego 59
article.story: LAS VEGAS -- Rayshawn Goins scored 15 points to help James Madison beat San Diego 62-59 in the Vegas Holiday Hoops Classic on Sunday. Devon Moore had 13 points, and A.J. Davis came off the bench to add 11. Moore and Taylor Bessick led with four rebounds apiece for the Dukes (6-6). The Dukes led 33-30 at halftime. The Dukes shot 45.5 percent from the field for the game, while the Toreros shot 44 percent. Johnny Dee led the Toreros (6-8) with 18 points. Chris Manresa had 10 points and 13 rebounds. Ken Rancifer had 11 points.
